"v.装病以逃避工作 【英】 v. 装病以逃避工作(to pretend to be ill in order to escape duty or work; shirk) 【考】 malingerer : duty / recluse : humanity(装病的人为了[逃避] 职责/隐士为了[逃避] 人类) 【记】 mal(坏)+linger(逗留 ，偷懒)→装病; 【同】 参考：malingerer(装 病逃避工作的人) 【例】 The second time the soldier malingered, he was forced to clean all the toilets. v. 装病以逃避责任或工作! 【记】mal坏, linger(v 逗留; 溜达)－装病 【参】malingerer(n 装病逃避工作的人); malnutrition(n 营养失调); malodorous(adj 有恶臭的); maltreat(v 虐待; 滥用); malpractice(n 玩忽职守) 【类】malingerer: duty = recluse: humanity = camouflage[dissemble]: detection装病的人逃避职责 = 隐士逃避人类 = 掩饰逃避发现parsimonious: skimp = malingering: shirk吝啬的人吝啬 = 诈病的人逃避hoard: miser = shirk: malinger守财奴秘藏 = 装病的人逃避 【记】mal 坏，恶意 + linger拖延 【相关】linger 逗留, 闲荡, 拖延, 游移 malinger (v.)  1820, from French malingrer ""to suffer,"" perhaps also ""pretend to be ill,"" from malingre ""ailing, sickly"" (13c.), of uncertain origin, possibly a blend of mingre ""sickly, miserable"" and malade ""ill."" Mingre is itself a blend of maigre ""meager"" + haingre ""sick, haggard,"" possibly from Germanic (compare Middle High German hager ""thin""). The sense evolution may be through notion of beggars with sham sores. Related: Malingered; malingering; malingerer (1785)."
